There's one nitpick from CodeRabbit about Biome linting:

In `src/lib/markdown.ts` lines 620-622, the forEach arrow callbacks implicitly return the result of the inner `forEach()` call. Biome flags this because `forEach` callbacks shouldn't return values. The fix is to add braces to the arrow callbacks.

The fix is:
```diff
-  allPosts.forEach((post) => post.tags.forEach(add));
-  allFlows.forEach((flow) => flow.tags.forEach(add));
-  allNotes.forEach((note) => note.tags.forEach(add));


+  allPosts.forEach((post) => { post.tags.forEach(add); });
+  allFlows.forEach((flow) => { flow.tags.forEach(add); });
+  allNotes.forEach((note) => { note.tags.forEach(add); });
```

There are also two "failed checks" to address. The docstring coverage check is flagging 0% coverage when 80% is required, but this appears to be a misconfigured check that doesn't really apply to this TypeScript project—the codebase doesn't use docstrings and it's a project-wide issue rather than something specific to this PR. The title check also failed, though the details got cut off.

The docstring and title issues aren't really code changes I need to make. I should focus on fixing the actual Biome linting issue instead. Let me check what the current state of those lines looks like in markdown.ts.

